Summer Athletic Programs Information:

There will be a meeting for students (going into 9th-12th grades) who are planning on participating in ANY sport this coming school year on Tuesday, June 16th at 5:00pm at the football field.

Students must stay 6 feet apart at all times.

Students will be broken up into smaller groups to meet with their individual coaches. Parents are welcomed to attend.

When summer activities begin, all programs will meet the safety guidelines we have been given from the MHSAA and State of Michigan.

We are very excited to see our students again!

Go Knights!

Norway High School Yearbooks – (Deadline is June 15th)

- All Yearbooks are completed and ready to be ordered!

Attached is the Norway High School Yearbook order form. Please indicate what year/years you would like to purchase on the form. Both 2020 and 2019 yearbooks are indicated on the form however, we do have a surplus of 2018 and 2017 yearbooks ($55) so those are available as well. Please use the same order form, but write the year you would like at the top. If you would like multiple years, please indicate which years you would like and the correct payment amount.

Yearbooks will be ordered promptly after the deadline, so please make sure to get your orders in! Yearbooks will not be ordered without payment.

Please mail the order form and payment to:

Norway High School
Attn: Yearbook
300 Section Street
Norway, MI 49870

You can also drop the forms and payments off on Tuesday’s from 11:00-12:30 during meal pick-up.

Thank you!

Norway Music Boosters
June 3 at 11:30 AM ·

The band and chorus rooms will be open next week for 6th through 12th grade students to return instruments, music, uniforms, binders, folders, and books.

Tuesday, June 9th, --> 11am until 4pm

Wednesday, June 10th --> 4pm until 6pm

Ms. Ware will check over your items to make sure they are in good condition and cross you off of the list so we can keep accurate records of who has turned in what.

DO NOT leave items in the office, mailboxes, sitting outside the door, etc. You will be charged for missing items if we cannot verify what you turned in. Please address any questions to kware@nvknights.org

(times are designed to align with iPad returns so you can accomplish both at the same time)

post_text: So proud of these students!!
shared_text:
Norway Music Boosters
May 21 at 11:22 AM ·

Congratulations to our senior music scholarship recipients Austyn Hart and Mary Slagle!

After the passing of former band director Mr. Tim Recla, the Band Boosters at that time decided to start a scholarship, in his memory, for a graduating band student to use to further their education. When the Band Boosters became the Music Boosters this scholarship was expanded to include one chorus student as well.

Both of our recipients have made us proud through their active service to the music department and the local community. We look forward to seeing where the next step of their educational journey takes them!

post_text:
2020 Senior Highlight

John Mattia

John's favorite class was Art. He loved to express his ideas and creativity through his drawings.

While in school, John participated in a work study program, Graphic Arts class at the vocational center, volunteered in the concession stand at athletic events.

Some of John's favorite memories at school involved beating Mr. Adams in Cars Racing when they were allowed to bring their games systems to school, and also the time Mr. Adams had to wear John's Packer Jersey for the day as a result in loosing a race against John. John also really enjoyed when the entire football team sat with him during the homecoming lunch picnic. John's favorite summer was spent hanging out with his friend Parker.

John would like to especially thank Ms. Popp for never giving up on him and always being in his corner.

After high school, John plans to participate in a community based work program, attend Bay De Noc college and eventually continue on to Michigan Career and Technical Institute.

We wish you the best and will miss you John!

#knightpride #uknighted

Attention NVAS Parents and Students:

The NVAS buildings will be open for EK-8 parents and 9-12 students or parents to enter the building and pick up ESSENTIAL personal and educational belongings from their lockers. This will take place during the days and times below.

Wednesday, April 8th - 8:00am - 3:30pm
Thursday, April 9th - 8:00am - 3:30pm

We still plan on having a "regular" cleanout day (May or June) once the COVID-19 emergency subsides. Personal belongings can also be picked up then.

Parents/students will only be allowed in each building 4 at a time and must take all precautions that are currently implemented in the state of Michigan. Visitors will be buzzed in as usual.

The use of gloves and masks of anyone that enters the building is highly recommended and students and parents are asked to not congregate or stay in the building any longer than needed.

High School - Use entrance "J" only
Middle School - Use entrance "C" only
Elementary - Use entrance "A" only

Thank you and please stay safe and healthy!

post_text: Norway-Vulcan Area Schools student Callie Paul did an amazing job with her #20Time project by planning, scheduling and running a #MysterySkype in the classroom with our 4th grade students last Thursday. Students got to ask questions to their ‘mystery location’ classroom back and forth via video conferencing until they figured out each other’s locations. Check out the video to find out the mystery spot! This is a great way to incorporate technology and global learning into the classroom. They are planning an international video visit next! Great job Callie! We are so proud of you!

post_text:
The Norway Calculus class has been working on optimization problems. They were assigned a problem where they were given the dimensions of a piece of paper and had to design a box from that paper that would hold a maximum volume. The students then needed to actually construct their box. The class decided to take it a step further by decorating their boxes and putting Secret Santa gifts inside.

Back Row (Left to Right): Nathan Paulitch, Hunter McCarthy, Alex Heigl, Shane Groeneveld, Raina Menghini, Ethan Sabotta, Trevor Dapoz
Middle Row (Left to Right): Mark Gays, Mary Slagle, McKenna Neuens, Allison Olson
Bottom Row (Left to Right): Danae Anderson, Paige Chartier, Libby Lofholm, Callie Paul

post_text:
Norway High School senior Mary Slagle, the daughter of Tami Slagle and Tom Slagle of Norway, has been selected by the Norway High School faculty as the nominee for the DAR (Daughters of the American Revolution) Good Citizen Program.

Mary is the Key Club President, YAC (Youth Advisory Committee) President; LEO Club President; Student Council Secretary, Red Cross Blood Drive Student Coordinator and Cheer Captain. She is a member of the National Honor Society and participates in Big Brothers/Big Sisters. She is in Yearbook, Spanish Club, Art Club, and Drama Club. Mary also participates in Competitive Cheer, Sideline Cheer, and Golf.

After graduating high school Mary plans to attend college to purse a degree in math and science in secondary education. She is self-motivated, has a strong work ethic, and is very dependable.
